709409f-a.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 27th Street (West)
709409f-a.text:
804-808 (old Nos. 454-458) Sixth Ave., east side, between West 27th and
28th Streets. The centre portion of building (Moquins Restaurant) is a
4-story frame house.
About 1916.
Brown Brothers.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

709406f-b.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 27th Street (West)
709406f-b.text:
Sixth ~-venue, north from W. 27th Street, showing the
Sixth Avenue ''El'' demolition at that point. The 28th Street
station appears preparatory to stripping.
Across same appears,an office building at the N.W. corner
of this thorougnfare and s. 31st Street; the Hotel McAlpin and
the Colonial Building.
View No. 3 shows only the west side of this Avenue with
its various enterpr126s.
Jan. 20, 1939
Views: 1-2-3
P. L. Sperr
NO REPROODUCTIONS

709407f-a.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 27th Street (West)
709407f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 27th Street, showing same be-
fore and after the demolition of the old ''gg'' structure. The
station seen is at 28th Sgreet. Note the streetcar under same.
These were removed and transportation is now provided for by
buses. The later view has the towering Empite State Building in
its background.
January 29, 1928
March 29, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO R2PRODUCTIONS
The samme as above, from another angle.
P. L. Sperr  September 27, 1940
